            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.23.13_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">13</fw>
                
                As from Andrew Nelson <unclear>Lire</unclear>
                11 Strattford <unclear>avenue</unclear>
                London W1
                
                29 May 1953
                
                    <salute>My dear John Neihardt&#8212;</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I cannot thank you enough for the lovely <hi rend="caps">"PRIMER OF MEDIEVAL LATIN"</hi> which reached me safely yesterday. I shall long treasure this work with partiuclar attention + remembrance of you + your <unclear>kindness</unclear>. My silence of late has been caused <hi rend="caps">A</hi>)- + largely - by overwork: 14 hours a day on most days: sending me home half dead to fall asleep on the evening mail or papers: <hi rend="caps">B</hi>) a poisoned gland in my throat&#8212; which upset me considerably &#8212; <unclear>in</unclear> the <unclear>heart</unclear> the treatment <unclear>I've</unclear>!- for the better part of this last month. Now I am a lot better, but very very tired. <unclear>I've</unclear> had no holiday for 5 years &#8212; a long time in view of the intense + heavy work I've been doing &#8212; So <del/> <unclear>next</unclear> week I'm off to the wilds of Connemara &#8212; which is north of the famous <hi rend="underline"><hi rend="caps">GALWAY BAY</hi></unclear> in <unclear/> I'll be in the real wild &#8212; just the thing I love. I'm going to spy on the land &#8212; in the archelological sense &#8212; for Cambridge University + I'm going to collect flora for The Natural History Museum, + for the Royal Botanical Gardens at Kew. So I'll be happy + busy. Did you ever send me the <hi rend="underline">Stone War-club</hi> you promised? I ask simply because I've never had it &#8212; and you may be (if <unclear>you <hi rend="underline">did</hi></unclear> send it) thinking what an impolite + discourteous person I am! I feel guilty in not acknowledging the
                    
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.23.13_0002a"/>
                    
                    <fw type="authorial">2</fw>
                    
                    charming lovable letter from your dear daughter. But, and its true, I've been so swamped with work that the pleasures of personal contact + correspondence have been denied me! My life, in <hi rend="underline">that</hi> sense, has gone to hell in the last 3 months. Still, my spirit's all right &#8212; only I do wish there was <hi rend="underline">25</hi> hours in the day.</hi>
                    
                    With loving + affectionate greetings to Mrs <hi rend="caps">N.</hi> yourself + family &#8212;
                    
                    <salute>Yours ever</salute>
                    <signed>James</signed>
                </closer>
                    
                    <note type="curatorial" place="bottom"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
                    
